The paper focuses on software engineering and specifically on detecting code migrations between Java third-party libraries. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing code fragments and collecting library documentation, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SD (Software Development). The evaluation of the tool's accuracy could be considered as a machine learning task, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the tool involves searching for specific code fragments, which could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
